> The Newsroom is an American television political drama series created and
> principally written by Aaron Sorkin that premiered on HBO on June 24, 2012, and
> concluded on December 14, 2014, consisting of 25 episodes over three seasons.
> The series chronicles the behind-the-scenes events at the fictional Atlantis
> Cable News (ACN) channel. It features an ensemble cast including Jeff Daniels as
> anchor Will McAvoy, who, together with his staff, sets out to put on a news show
> "in the face of corporate and commercial obstacles and their own personal
> entanglements".
